# data/book.txt — drop your book here before running ingest
#
# How to use:
#   1. Copy or paste your book's full plain text into a file named  data/book.txt
#      (this file is a template — rename or copy it).
#   2. UTF-8 encoding, no special formatting needed. Project Gutenberg downloads
#      (.txt) work great out of the box.
#   3. Run:  npm run ingest
#      This reads data/book.txt → calls Claude → writes data/bible.json
#   4. Start the app:  npm run dev
#
# Limits:
#   • Default max: 200 000 characters (roughly a full novel). Override with
#     MAX_BOOK_CHARS=500000 npm run ingest
#   • data/book.txt is gitignored (copyrighted content stays local).
#
# Example first lines (replace with your book):

The Project Gutenberg EBook of Pride and Prejudice, by Jane Austen

CHAPTER 1

It is a truth universally acknowledged, that a single man in possession of
a good fortune, must be in want of a wife.
